  "doc_id": "4430",
  "text": "Pregnant women infected with L. monocytogenes may experience only a mild flulike illness, with fever, headache, myalgias, and occasionally gastrointestinal symptoms. Prodromal illness may affect two-thirds of women with listeriosis complicating pregnancy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The symptoms correspond to the bacteremic phase of infection and represent the time when blood cultures should be taken to permit diagnosis.",
